&TUTORIAL ---------- BACKGROUND COBOL - LISTING -----------------------
&NEXT SELECTION ===>%SELECT                             &
$
$THERE ARE TWO TYPES OF LISTINGS GENERATED BY THE COBOL COMPILER:
$
$ &1$- LIST OUTPUT
$ &2$- TERMINAL OUTPUT
$
$
$  LIST OUTPUT IS DIRECTED TO A SYSOUT QUEUE FOR PRINTING ON A HIGH SPEE
$  PRINTER.  TERMINAL OUTPUT WILL ALWAYS BE DIRECTED TO A TEMPORARY DATA
$
$  THE COMPILER OPTIONS "LIST" AND "TERM" DETERMINE IF THE COBOL COMPILE
$  WILL GENERATE LIST OR TERM OUTPUT.
<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8)
                  LIST (    1,    2)
                RETURN (HJOB221,HJOB222);
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('HJOB2   ');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('HJOB23  ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('HJOB221 ');
<END>
